cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.SE

This paper discusses the impact of articles published in predatory journals, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with issues related to academic publishing and citation analysis. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also relevant as it deals with the retrieval and analysis of scholarly articles. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CY (Cybersecurity) are less likely but still possible as they deal with issues related to fraud and deception. cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also a possibility as it deals with quality assurance and testing, which is relevant to the quality of research published in journals.
